Start by cloning the starter code from the repo below.

https://gitlab.com/cit_4640/4640-w10-lab-start-w25

Setup:

add a new ssh public key to your AWS account using the "scripts/import_lab_key" script

create a new AMI using the Packer and Ansible configuration

Tasks:

Breakout the creation of the EC2 instance from the Terraform configuration into a new module "web-server".

include variables for the following in your modules:

- project name
- ami
- instance type (with t2.micro default)
- key name
- vpc security group ids (list(string))
- subnet id

include outputs for the following in your module

- instance ip address
- instance dns name
- instance id

In root main use:

- the local for project name defined in the root main
- the ami for the instance created by the Packer template
- default instance type
- the key imported with the import script
- the vpc security group defined in main
- the subnet id defined in main

output all outputs from the module in root main.

Deliverables:

Submit the a public Git repository that contains the following:

Things ending in "/" are directories.

- terraform/
- main.tf
- provider.tf
- modules/
- web-server/
- main.tf
- variables.tf
- outputs.tf

Clean Up:

Run terraform destroy

Remove your AMI and snapshot built with Packer

Delete the ssh key you used for the lab.
